    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-09-09T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-09-09T13:00:00-05:00" n="71"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d71">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">851G.00/8–746: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Consul at Saigon</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Reed</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-09-09T14:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 9, 1946—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>241. Intelligence reports of uncertain reliability state USSR (<hi rend="italic"
                        >a</hi>) anxious see Ho Chi Minh succeed unite three <gloss target="#t_ky1"
                        >Ky</gloss>s under Viet Nam for possible eventual weapon against National
                    Govt China and (<hi rend="italic">b</hi>) has instructed French Communists
                    manoeuvre reliable French Officers to Indochina for training cadres future Viet
                    Nam army. Keep <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> informed indications
                    subservience to Party line by Ho and other leaders, relative strength Communist
                    and non-Communist elements Viet Nam, and contacts with Communists other
                    countries. Inform O’Sullivan. Sent Saigon. Repeated Paris<note n="59"
                        xml:id="d71fn1">As telegram 4680.</note> for <gloss target="#t_Info1"
                        >info</gloss>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Clayton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
